<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Bars 0-4 (phrase A): F#m and D establish the submediant opening; E7→A cadences
- Bars 5-9 (repeat A): Inversions varied — F#m 2nd inv, Bm quartal, richer E7
- Bars 10-11 (phrase B bridge): C#m introduces the relative major coloring
- Bars 12-17 (coda): Descending motion D→E→A, then F#m→C#m→D convergence
- Bar 17 final: Bb substituted with Bm (nearest diatonic) for lever harp compatibility

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 0→1: A3 in LH (F#m) steps to B2 (Bm) — smooth bass contrary to falling melody
- Bar 4: E7 to A — textbook V7→I resolution with G#3→A2 in bass
- Bar 10-11: C#m→E→F#m→Bm→A creates a descending thirds sequence in LH bass
- Bar 16→17: D→Bm final cadence, contrary motion between hands

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-2: medium texture (2+3 notes), spacious with rests in bar 2
- Bars 3-4: busier with one-chord-per-beat motion
- Bars 5-9: varied inversions to distinguish the repeat
- Bars 10-14: climax with E→A strong cadences, 3-note RH
- Bars 15-17: settling, final chord Bm as sub for Bb
-->
